                <h2>Van Gogh's Life and Struggles</h2>
                <p>Van Gogh faced numerous mental health issues throughout his life, which profoundly influenced both his art and his existence. His famous severed ear is one of the most remembered episodes of his tumultuous life. He went through periods of deep depression and crises, which led to him being admitted to sanatoriums several times. Despite this, he continued to paint incessantly, creating more than 2,100 works of art, including 860 oil paintings, in the short period of his artistic career, which lasted just a decade.</p>
            </div>
